Step 1: Identify the Net Profit from the income statement.  
• Net Profit = –1,669,849.77  

Step 2: Identify the Total Assets at the beginning and end from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Total Assets = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 14,066,175.95  

Step 3: Compute the Average Total Assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
  = (13,000,000.00 + 14,066,175.95) / 2  
  = 27,066,175.95 / 2  
  ≈ 13,533,087.98  

Step 4: Calculate the Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit ÷ Average Total Assets) × 100  
  = (–1,669,849.77 ÷ 13,533,087.98) × 100  
  ≈ –12.35%  

The final answer is:
